item.title: Jan add a quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald
item.description: "She’s got an indiscreet voice,” I remarked. “It’s full of-“ I hesitated. “Her voice is full of money,” he said suddenly. That was it. I’d never understood before. It was full of money-that was the inexhaustible charm that rose and fell in it, the jingle of it, the cymbals’ song of it." -- F. Scott Fitzgerald

item.title: Jan add a quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald
item.description: "What'll we do with ourselves this afternoon?” cried Daisy, “and the day after that, and the next thirty years?" -- F. Scott Fitzgerald

item.title: Jan add a quote by F. Scott Fitzgerald
item.description: "Look at that,' she whispered, and then after a moment: 'I'd like to just get one of those pink clouds and put you in it and push you around." -- F. Scott Fitzgerald
